HEADWORD: Reneye
<hw>Re*neye"</hw> <pr>(r?-n?")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Renay</er>.]</ety> <def>To deny; to reject; to renounce.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For he made every man <qex>reneye</qex> his law.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reng</ent>⟦br⟧
